keyValuePair.Value: How will you approach your remaining games?
Promotion's now beyond your boys but there are still games ahead before the end of the season. What will your approach be? Can these fixtures be useful at all?
We won't stop playing, I promise.
It's disappointing to miss out on promotion but there are positives to take from the season. We can relax and play our football now and, perhaps, give some young players a chance.
It's disappointing to miss out on promotion but there are positives to take from the season. We can relax and play our football now and, perhaps, give some young players a chance.
Let's be professional.
We're disappointed, but these players have professional pride. We won't let our heads drop. The boys will want to win games and end the season on a high.
There's plenty to play for.
I think the lads understand the situation. There'll be changes at the club at the end of the season, so they know that, in the next few games, they'll be playing for their futures.
What's left to play for?
Your relegation's now been confirmed and there's huge disappointment around the club. How will you approach your remaining fixtures now? What is there to play for?
We owe good displays to our fans.
Of course everybody's disappointed. I think we owe it to our fans to go into games with a professional attitude. A couple of wins could lift our hopes for next season.
Of course everybody's disappointed. I think we owe it to our fans to go into games with a professional attitude. A couple of wins could lift our hopes for next season.
Next season starts here.
We've failed, haven't we? But we have to go into the remaining games with some motivation. It'll be as if this is the start of all the hard work we'll need to do come next season.
The players have a point to prove.
I want these players to convince me they should be here next season. The division below will be a real challenge. Have these boys got the right attitude to take us back up?
You've just fallen short. What now?
It's been a challenging season for everybody at the club, and you've come through some difficult spells together. How will you want your team to approach your remaining games?
We can go out and play our football.
We didn't quite fulfil our ambitions for the season, but we can't feel sorry for ourselves. The pressure's off now. I want us to go out and show our fans what we're capable of.
We didn't quite fulfil our ambitions for the season, but we can't feel sorry for ourselves. The pressure's off now. I want us to go out and show our fans what we're capable of.
We won't sulk, that's for sure.
Yes, we came up short in the end. But we won't let our heads drop. We owe it to our supporters to do everything we can to finish the season on a high note.
There's plenty still at stake.
Do the lads need motivation? They shouldn't. We've didn't reach our targets, and so they need to work to convince me that they're ready to be part of what we want to do in the future.
You've missed out on Europe. What now?
You kept battling away, but qualifying for Europe is beyond you now. Will the rest of the season go flat? Or is there still something to play for in your remaining games.
There's always something to play for
Of course we're all disappointed but we've got plenty to play for. Our professional pride, for a start. We have to go out and entertain the fans. We want them behind us next season.
Of course we're all disappointed but we've got plenty to play for. Our professional pride, for a start. We have to go out and entertain the fans. We want them behind us next season.
Let's be positive.
This is a disappointing moment, for sure. But myself, the staff and the team are all committed to finishing the season strongly now. We owe that much to our fans.
I'm looking to the future.
Yes, I'm sorry to miss out. But I don't want my players letting their heads go down. We've got work to do. The lads need to go out and prove they have a part to play in this club's future.
How will you finish the season now?
The prize of a top-half finish is out of your reach now. There must be a danger of the rest of the season just petering out. How will you approach your remaining games?
Let's relax and play our football.
It's been a difficult season and I think the pressure told on us in the end. Let's relax now, play our football, and finish the season positively if we can.

We'll be positive going forward.
Yes, we've under-achieved, but I think there are positives to take from the season. I hope we can at least play some decent football and entertain our fans in the games that are left.
We'll see who wants to succeed here.
We aren't where we wanted to be, but I think the lads still have plenty to play for. In these remaining games, I want to see who's committed to bringing success to the club in the future.
You can't make the playoffs. What now for the team?
The fans kept hoping, but it's now impossible for your boys to reach the playoffs. Is that the season over, then? How will you approach your remaining games?
Let's try and lift those supporters.
I think everybody recognises how hard we worked. And I'm sorry we missed out on the playoffs. I want to make sure the fans at least get to enjoy a positive end to the season now.

We'll be professional.

I want us to put on a show.

Let's remind people how good we are.

Can you lift yourselves for these last few games?

We still have plenty to prove.
